}}'''Nicaragua''' is a [[Nations|country]] that was added to [[BitLife: Life Simulator|BitLife]] in July 10, 2022.

On July 10, 2022, new countries were added to both iOS and Android. Along with Nicaragua, there was also [[Andorra]], [[Angola]], [[Aruba]], [[Belize]], [[El Salvador]], [[Guatemala]], [[Guyana]], [[Haiti]], [[Papua New Guinea]], [[Paraguay]], [[Samoa]], [[Tunisia]], and [[Uganda]]. This was added in a bug fix update prior to the upcoming Business Update.

==Information==
Nicaragua, along with Haiti, Pakistan, Afghanistan, Angola, Venezuela, Syria, Iraq, Tunisia, Uganda, and Papua New Guinea, is one of the countries where a player can die from a sudden terrorist attack, giving them the Unlucky ribbon.

